   \sum_{k=1}^n \frac{1}{\sqrt{k}} \ge \sum_{k=1}^n \frac{1}{\sqrt{k} + \sqrt{k-1}} =      \sum_{k=1}^n \frac{\sqrt{k} - \sqrt{k-1}}{(\sqrt{k} + \sqrt{k-1})(\sqrt{k} - \sqrt{k-1})} = \sum_{k=1}^n (\sqrt{k} - \sqrt{k-1}) = \sqrt{n} 
